column3: feedbacks
Thank you for the opportunity to participate in this study!
Fun!! I want to do more
Good.
This was pretty difficult, but I hope I did well!

The instructions are kinda confusing.  Instead of a quick example on the sidebar, you should include an example already filled out that is similar to the exact ones we are working on.  Best of luck to you!
this was a little bit confusing in how it was worded and also with the short timer was hard to get through everything; I felt like I was rushing because of the timer..
Thanks for the HIT!  I did my best and hope the data is useful!  This is my first time doing on of these tasks so please don't judge too harshly.
Very interesting, I hope I can qualify to do more.
more time!
I hope I did this right! Thank you for allowing me to try my best!
I did the best I could with what I had. The examples are a little confusing and so are the directions.
Interesting HIT.

I think this HIT needs a longer timer, like at least an hour, because when working on mturk people often accept tasks while working on other ones and they won't have enough time if they don't get to this one immediately. And I feel like it would be easier if we were supposed to select the correct claim. The opposite logic made it harder to conceptualize the task at first glance.
Had to think about these! Thanks!
cool hit
I think more explanations/examples would have been helpful.
I did find the wording of the instructions a bit confusing at first.
This was more difficult than I thought.
This hit needs a longer timer - it takes more than 8 minutes to do some thinking about these situations.
Timer is way too short. Also, the ambiguity in some of the claims was troublesome. Without more information, the claim could go either way.
Maybe it would be useful to give slightly more time to complete the HIT to not make us rush through the claims and think carefully

no problems
